<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Dorsum of body with distinct reticulations that consist of small triangles arranged in polygons; median frontal tubercle distinctly protuberant, rectangular; antennal tubercles each with a cylindrical process at inner apex, higher than median frontal tubercle; dorsal setae of abdomen sparse and short, with small setal tubercles.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Apterous viviparous females: body elliptical (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Aspidophorodon reticulatum Qiao &amp; Xu, sp. nov. Apterous viviparous female A dorsal view of body B dorsal view of head C antenna D ultimate rostral segment E hind tibia and tarsi F reticulations formed by strings of small triangles arranged in polygons on abdominal tergites G siphunculus H cauda I anal plate J genital plate. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702344" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9A</figureCitation>
), green in life.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Mounted specimens.</emphasis>
Body pale, PT, distal part of rostrum, tarsi, distal parts of SIPH, cauda, anal plate and genital plate pale brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Aspidophorodon reticulatum Qiao &amp; Xu, sp. nov. Apterous viviparous female A dorsal view of body B dorsal view of head C antenna D ultimate rostral segment E hind tibia and tarsi F reticulations formed by strings of small triangles arranged in polygons on abdominal tergites G siphunculus H cauda I anal plate J genital plate. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702344" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9A</figureCitation>
). Thoracic nota and abdominal tergites I-VIII each with one pair of spinal sclerites, pale brown in color, other parts pale in color (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Aspidophorodon reticulatum Qiao &amp; Xu, sp. nov. Apterous viviparous female A dorsal view of body B dorsal view of head C antenna D ultimate rostral segment E hind tibia and tarsi F reticulations formed by strings of small triangles arranged in polygons on abdominal tergites G siphunculus H cauda I anal plate J genital plate. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702344" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9A, F</figureCitation>
). See Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="T2" captionText="Table 2. Morphometric data about species of the nominate subgenus (in mm)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/B3A3829737B001A4C9C95E6A9EF3E9E9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableUuid="B3A3829737B001A4C9C95E6A9EF3E9E9">2</tableCitation>
for general measurements.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Head</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Ocular tubercles small. Dorsum of head covered with wrinkles between compound eyes, anterior part with weak wrinkles (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Aspidophorodon reticulatum Qiao &amp; Xu, sp. nov. Apterous viviparous female A dorsal view of head B antenna C ultimate rostral segment D reticulations formed by strings of small triangles arranged in polygons on abdominal tergites E siphunculus F cauda G anal plate H genital plate. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702343" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">8A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Aspidophorodon reticulatum Qiao &amp; Xu, sp. nov. Apterous viviparous female A dorsal view of body B dorsal view of head C antenna D ultimate rostral segment E hind tibia and tarsi F reticulations formed by strings of small triangles arranged in polygons on abdominal tergites G siphunculus H cauda I anal plate J genital plate. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702344" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9B</figureCitation>
). Median frontal tubercle distinctly protuberant, rectangular (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Aspidophorodon reticulatum Qiao &amp; Xu, sp. nov. Apterous viviparous female A dorsal view of head B antenna C ultimate rostral segment D reticulations formed by strings of small triangles arranged in polygons on abdominal tergites E siphunculus F cauda G anal plate H genital plate. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702343" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">8A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Aspidophorodon reticulatum Qiao &amp; Xu, sp. nov. Apterous viviparous female A dorsal view of body B dorsal view of head C antenna D ultimate rostral segment E hind tibia and tarsi F reticulations formed by strings of small triangles arranged in polygons on abdominal tergites G siphunculus H cauda I anal plate J genital plate. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702344" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9B</figureCitation>
), with one pair of long and pointed setae on venter. Antennal tubercles undeveloped, each with a cylindrical, slightly wrinkled process at inner apex, higher than median frontal tubercle, each process with a short and pointed seta at apex (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Aspidophorodon reticulatum Qiao &amp; Xu, sp. nov. Apterous viviparous female A dorsal view of head B antenna C ultimate rostral segment D reticulations formed by strings of small triangles arranged in polygons on abdominal tergites E siphunculus F cauda G anal plate H genital plate. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702343" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">8A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Aspidophorodon reticulatum Qiao &amp; Xu, sp. nov. Apterous viviparous female A dorsal view of body B dorsal view of head C antenna D ultimate rostral segment E hind tibia and tarsi F reticulations formed by strings of small triangles arranged in polygons on abdominal tergites G siphunculus H cauda I anal plate J genital plate. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702344" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9B</figureCitation>
). Dorsal setae of head short and slightly blunt, with small setal tubercles. Head with one pair of cephalic setae, one pair of dorsal setae between antennae and two pairs of dorsal setae between compounds eyes arranged transversely. Antennae 5-segmented, Ant. I-III smooth, Ant. IV-V with imbrications (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Aspidophorodon reticulatum Qiao &amp; Xu, sp. nov. Apterous viviparous female A dorsal view of head B antenna C ultimate rostral segment D reticulations formed by strings of small triangles arranged in polygons on abdominal tergites E siphunculus F cauda G anal plate H genital plate. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702343" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">8B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Aspidophorodon reticulatum Qiao &amp; Xu, sp. nov. Apterous viviparous female A dorsal view of body B dorsal view of head C antenna D ultimate rostral segment E hind tibia and tarsi F reticulations formed by strings of small triangles arranged in polygons on abdominal tergites G siphunculus H cauda I anal plate J genital plate. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702344" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9C</figureCitation>
); Ant. I slightly projected at inner apex. Antennal setae short and pointed, Ant. I-V with 3-4, 3, 1-2, 1, 1-2 (base) +1 (PT) setae, respectively; apex of PT usually with two setae. Primary rhinaria ciliated. Rostrum reaching mid-coxae; URS wedge-shaped (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Aspidophorodon reticulatum Qiao &amp; Xu, sp. nov. Apterous viviparous female A dorsal view of head B antenna C ultimate rostral segment D reticulations formed by strings of small triangles arranged in polygons on abdominal tergites E siphunculus F cauda G anal plate H genital plate. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702343" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">8C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Aspidophorodon reticulatum Qiao &amp; Xu, sp. nov. Apterous viviparous female A dorsal view of body B dorsal view of head C antenna D ultimate rostral segment E hind tibia and tarsi F reticulations formed by strings of small triangles arranged in polygons on abdominal tergites G siphunculus H cauda I anal plate J genital plate. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.77912.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/702344" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">9D</figureCitation>
), with two pairs of primary setae and two pairs of accessory setae.
</paragraph>
